bol (str): The character used to pad the content to the terminal width. Default is '-'.\ntext_position (str): The alignment of the text within the banner. Can be 'CENTER', 'LEFT', or 'RIGHT'. Default is 'CENTER'.\n\nExample:\n\\>>> banner(\"hello world\", text_position=\"CENTER\")\n---- hello world ----\n\\>>> banner(\"hello world\", text_position=\"LEFT\")\nhello world ------------\n\\>>> banner(\"hello world\", text_position=\"RIGHT\")\n------------ hello world\n"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "donware.src.utils.images", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "donware.src.utils.images.trim_white_margins", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "dir_from", "type": {"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "dir_to", "type": {"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "white_tolerance", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Trims white margins from images in a directory, makes white pixels transparent, and saves the cropped images to a new directory.\n\nParameters:\ndir_from (Path): The source directory containing the images to be processed.\ndir_to (Path): The target directory where the processed images will be saved.\nwhite_tolerance (int): The tolerance level for white color detection (default is 10).\n\nExample:\n\\>>> from pathlib import Path\n\\>>> trim_white_margins(Path('input_images'), Path('output_images'), white_tolerance=15)\n\nInput:\n\\- A directory 'input_images' containing images with white margins.\n\nOutput:\n\\- A directory 'output_images' containing images with white margins cropped and white pixels made transparent.\n"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "donware.src.utils.latex", "documentation": ["!/Users/donyin/min